Installing Operators Using CLI (OpenShift)
Objective
Install and manage operators using CLI (oc command) instead of the web console.
In CLI installation you mainly work with OLM resources like:
•	CatalogSource
•	PackageManifest
•	OperatorGroup
•	Subscription
•	InstallPlan
•	ClusterServiceVersion (CSV)
________________________________________
1️⃣ Steps to Install an Operator (CLI Flow)
To install an operator with CLI you generally follow this sequence:
Find operator
     ↓
Check operator details
     ↓
Choose channel
     ↓
Create namespace (optional)
     ↓
Create OperatorGroup
     ↓
Create Subscription
     ↓
OLM automatically creates:
  - InstallPlan
  - CSV
  - Operator deployment
Important concept:
👉 Admin only creates TWO resources
OperatorGroup
Subscription
OLM automatically creates everything else.
________________________________________
2️⃣ Operator Lifecycle Manager (OLM) Resources
OLM uses several resource types.
________________________________________
1️⃣ CatalogSource
CatalogSource tells OpenShift where operators are stored.
Example command:
oc get catalogsource -n openshift-marketplace
Example output:
NAME              DISPLAY
gls-catalog-cs    GLS Operator Catalog
Meaning:
•	Operators come from this catalog registry.
Namespace:
openshift-marketplace
________________________________________
2️⃣ PackageManifest
PackageManifest contains metadata of available operators.
List available operators:
oc get packagemanifests
Example output:
compliance-operator
file-integrity-operator
metallb-operator
lvms-operator
kubevirt-hyperconverged
This tells you:
👉 Which operators you can install.
________________________________________
3️⃣ Check Operator Details
To install an operator you need details like:
•	channel
•	source
•	namespace
•	install modes
Command:
oc describe packagemanifest lvms-operator -n openshift-marketplace
This shows detailed operator information.
________________________________________
Important Fields
1️⃣ Catalog Source
Catalog Source: gls-catalog-cs
Catalog Source Namespace: openshift-marketplace
This will be used in subscription YAML.
________________________________________
2️⃣ Available Channels
Example:
stable-4.18
Channel = version stream for updates
Example channels:
stable
fast
preview
________________________________________
3️⃣ Current CSV
lvms-operator.v4.18.1
CSV = operator version.
________________________________________
4️⃣ Description
Shows what the operator does.
Example:
Logical volume manager storage
________________________________________
5️⃣ Install Modes
Shows supported namespace modes.
Example:
OwnNamespace
SingleNamespace
MultiNamespace
AllNamespaces
Some operators support only specific modes.
________________________________________
6️⃣ Documentation Links
Example:
https://github.com/openshift/lvm-operator
Always check documentation before installation.
________________________________________
4️⃣ Create Namespace (Optional)
Operators run in a namespace.
Example:
oc create namespace openshift-storage
Some operators require specific namespaces.
Example:
openshift-storage
openshift-operators
________________________________________
5️⃣ OperatorGroup
OperatorGroup defines which namespaces the operator watches.
Example YAML:
apiVersion: operators.coreos.com/v1
kind: OperatorGroup
metadata:
  name: storage-operators
  namespace: openshift-storage
spec:
  targetNamespaces:
  - openshift-storage
Apply it:
oc apply -f operatorgroup.yaml
________________________________________
What this does
Operator will monitor:
openshift-storage
for custom resources.
________________________________________
Special Case
Namespace:
openshift-operators
already contains an OperatorGroup:
global-operators
This monitors all namespaces.
So normally you don't create a new OperatorGroup there.
________________________________________
6️⃣ Create Subscription
Subscription tells OLM:
Install this operator
Example YAML:
apiVersion: operators.coreos.com/v1alpha1
kind: Subscription
metadata:
  name: lvms-operator
  namespace: openshift-storage
spec:
  channel: stable-4.18
  name: lvms-operator
  source: gls-catalog-cs
  sourceNamespace: openshift-marketplace
  installPlanApproval: Automatic
Apply:
oc apply -f subscription.yaml
________________________________________
Important Fields
Field	Meaning
name	operator package name
channel	update channel
source	catalog source
sourceNamespace	where catalog exists
installPlanApproval	automatic/manual updates
________________________________________
7️⃣ What Happens After Subscription
Once subscription is created, OLM automatically creates:
InstallPlan
CSV
Operator deployment
________________________________________
8️⃣ InstallPlan
InstallPlan describes how the operator will be installed or updated.
Check:
oc get installplan -n openshift-storage
Example output:
install-pmh78
________________________________________
Manual Approval
If approval mode is:
Manual
You must approve installation.
Approve using:
oc patch installplan install-pmh78 \
--type merge \
-p '{"spec":{"approved":true}}' \
-n openshift-storage
________________________________________
9️⃣ ClusterServiceVersion (CSV)
CSV represents operator version installed.
Check:
oc get csv -n openshift-storage
Example:
lvms-operator.v4.18.1
CSV contains:
•	permissions
•	CRDs
•	deployments
•	metadata
________________________________________
🔟 Operator Resource
OLM also creates an Operator resource.
Check:
oc describe operator file-integrity-operator
Example output shows:
InstallPlan reference
Subscription reference
________________________________________
1️⃣1️⃣ Managing Operator Updates
Updates are controlled by:
spec.installPlanApproval
Two modes:
________________________________________
Automatic Updates
installPlanApproval: Automatic
OLM automatically updates operator.
________________________________________
Manual Updates
installPlanApproval: Manual
Admin must approve update.
________________________________________
Check pending updates
oc get installplan -n openshift-file-integrity
Example:
install-z5k2a   file-integrity-operator.v4.18.1   Manual   false
Meaning update waiting for approval.
________________________________________
Approve update
oc patch installplan install-z5k2a \
--type merge \
-p '{"spec":{"approved":true}}' \
-n openshift-file-integrity
________________________________________
1️⃣2️⃣ Change Update Channel
You can change the operator channel.
Example:
oc patch subscription file-integrity-operator \
-n openshift-file-integrity \
--type merge \
-p '{"spec":{"channel":"stable"}}'
If automatic updates enabled:
👉 update may start immediately.
________________________________________
1️⃣3️⃣ Using Operators
Operators manage Custom Resources.
Example:
Operator creates CRD like:
metallbs.metallb.io
You create custom resource instance to use operator.
________________________________________
Check CRDs created by operator
Example command:
oc get csv metallb-operator.v4.18.0 \
-o jsonpath="{.spec.customresourcedefinitions.owned[*].name}"
Output example:
ipaddresspools.metallb.io
bgppeers.metallb.io
l2advertisements.metallb.io
________________________________________
View CRD explanation
oc explain metallb
or
oc explain ipaddresspool
________________________________________
1️⃣4️⃣ Troubleshooting Operators
If installation fails check:
________________________________________
CSV status
oc get csv
Look for:
Succeeded
Failed
Pending
________________________________________
InstallPlan
oc get installplan
Check approval status.
________________________________________
Operator Pods
oc get pods -n <operator-namespace>
Example:
file-integrity-operator
________________________________________
Pod Logs
oc logs <operator-pod>
________________________________________
Events
oc get events
________________________________________
1️⃣5️⃣ Operator Workloads vs Managed Workloads
Very important concept.
________________________________________
Operator Workload
Created by OLM.
Example:
file-integrity-operator deployment
Purpose:
monitor custom resources
________________________________________
Managed Workloads
Created by operator.
Example:
daemonsets
statefulsets
pods
Example:
aide-fileintegrity daemonset
These run actual application tasks.
________________________________________
🔑 Key Exam Concepts
Remember these:
Resource	Role
CatalogSource	operator repository
PackageManifest	operator metadata
OperatorGroup	namespace scope
Subscription	installs operator
InstallPlan	installation/update plan
CSV	operator version definition
CRD	operator API
Custom Resource	instance of operator
________________________________________
🔥 Complete CLI Operator Installation Flow
oc get catalogsource
        ↓
oc get packagemanifests
        ↓
oc describe packagemanifest
        ↓
Create Namespace
        ↓
Create OperatorGroup
        ↓
Create Subscription
        ↓
OLM creates:
  InstallPlan
  CSV
  Operator Deployment
        ↓
Create Custom Resource
        ↓
Operator deploys application

